# React Component Conventions

- All components use `"use client"` directive (this is a client-rendered SPA)
- Define props via a `Props` interface — use named exports, not default exports
- Parent page (`app/page.tsx`) owns all state; components receive data and callbacks via props
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes only. Color palette: stone (neutrals) + orange (accent)
- Severity/status colors: import `SEVERITY_STYLES` and `STATUS_STYLES` maps from `@/types`
- Visual consistency: `rounded-lg`/`rounded-xl` corners, `shadow-sm` shadows, `border-stone-200` borders
- Enums and constants: import from `@/types` (frontend) — keep in sync with `lib/api.ts` (API)

See `components/CLAUDE.md` for detailed patterns.
